reviews.text: A great place for berry picking with a small, hardworking team running the show. Love the berries, the old school honor system for already-picked boxes and pumpkins out front. Looking forward to many more summers picking with my family.

This is a great place to pick berries! We picked blueberries here on wild blueberry weekend and there was ample space to pick and enjoy the day. Beautiful property and great, pleasant and personable people that own and operate the place. We will be back for more!

Check their Facebook page for updates about when they‚Äôre open for picking and what you can currently pick. We went and had a wonderful time. The man who owns the place was very friendly and taught us about the different varieties of blueberries they had. Was definitely a fun time!

We‚Äôve been loyal supporters of this small farm for years. Today my family and I decided to take our friends with their children blueberry picking. We accidentally ended up on a very poorly labeled area where we weren‚Äôt supposed to pick.
The employee drove up to us on a golf cart and started screaming at us, he yelled ‚ÄúI want you out of here, just get out!!! Get out of here! Get out!‚Äù

He didn‚Äôt simple tell us we shouldn‚Äôt pick there, he threw us out . Our children were so confused and frightened, my daughter started crying.
We apologized and explained that it‚Äôs an honest mistake, the sign wasn‚Äôt visible and we would never pick blueberries from a reserved area but he screamed at us to leave.
We have never been treated with this much hatred and aggression.

Warning: My young family took a trip berry picking today with another mom and her two young kids. The group took a wrong turn (by mistake) and ended up in an area of the farm that was labeled ‚Äúreserved‚Äù. A older male employee of the Farm showed up on a golf cart without warning and aggressively screamed. ‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt be here! Get Out! Get Out! You have to leave now! I don‚Äôt even want your money you have to leave!‚Äù They tried to calmly explain that it was an honest mistake but he was agitated and angry. Our kids were completely shocked by this type of behavior from an adult. My wife and the other mom were speaking Russian before the incident and I would hate to think that that was the cause of this outburst on the part of the employee but that is the only explanation.

placeDetails.name: Chase Farms

reviews.text: Great place to buy some of the produce that they grow without pesticides. They also have a fabulous collection of pumpkins and unique squash for Halloween and Thanksgiving displays. For holiday cheer they have apple cider and donuts available!

We found Chase Farms quite by accident a few years ago while out and about on a scenic drive and since then we have been going back every year for our fall mums, cornstalks, Indian corn and pumpkins!  We love this place!  Everyone is so nice and helpful and if you happen to go when they are making the cider donuts - have a warm one!  It wouldn't be fall without a visit to Chase Farms!
First time to visit farm today. We look forward to trying their 'all' fruit spreads. We bought blueberry and peach. Enjoyed the view
We got some needed produce, and enjoyed hotdogs by the fire.

A favorite stop every time I‚Äôm visiting family in the area. Their own farm products are always outstanding, and they do a great job of rounding out their selection with other produce and local products. Their bakery is pretty great too!

I am definitely biased, but this is hands down the best farm stand in at least the surrounding three towns. The only other stands even comparable to this one are under the same ownership and management -- sweetest freaking corn you'll ever have in your life. They carry lean, fresh ground beef, and the produce assortment is constantly changing with the seasons. üëè The farmers that own this farm are some of the nicest, hardest working people you will ever meet.

I love this family owned farm, and the vegetables are amazing. Best vegetables around. Amazing people. I love supporting our local own family oriented businesses.  Wish we could buy vegetables all year around. I look forward to them every summer. üåΩü•ïü•íü•îüçÖüçÜü´õüßÑü´öü´ëüçâüçàü´ê
Nice, fresh produce. The sweet corn is especially good. Reasonable prices. We drive from Sanford and it's always worth the trip.
They offer not only fresh vegetables but also fresh meats! This is absolutely the best corn on the cobb I have ever had. Love the selection, and no place has better vegetables.

This is a local farming family.  It has everything you need and the quality is  great.  They carry honey from local people, meat and meat pies that are excellent.   The corn is soooo sweet.   Everyone who works there is very friendly.  Highly recommend the visit.
Very cute farm store with a self-service checkout station. Off season they have pies, prepared dishes, sauces, jams, syrup, and some herb and tomato plant starters that look very health (May 2025)
Five acre farm is fabulous. They offer an expanding array of plants, farm-fresh baked products: best ever fruit pies and loaded chix pot pie.
Hidden gem in Goose Rocks beach area of Kennebunkport. Fresh baked pies, cookies, and other baked treats. The blueberry pie is a standout!

We love this place. My wife and I go often, sometimes just to see what they have. You may find eggs, honey, yogurt, sweet treats, and can order pies. It is really cool. They also have lots of plants and trees for the holidays!

Love this place so much!! Try to swing by as much as possible just to see what‚Äôs new! Honor system and cash only (or check). Quality plants, fresh cut flowers, pies / baked goods and other treats like cookies and zucchini bread. Must visit!

placeDetails.name: Frith Farm

reviews.text: Self service farm stand and CSA. Beautiful location and offer reasonably price plants, including perennials and veg garden plants.

Great place to get fresh organic vegetables!  The staff is friendly and accommodating offering up advice and details on their farming skills.  The farm stand is self-service with nice displays of freshly picked vegetables.  Worth a stop when in the area!
Terrific farm! Truly enjoyed my first visit here.
I love this farm.  We get our veggies here.  The no-till farming is impressive.  Plus there's kittens.
What a beautiful organic, no till operation. Can't wait for their class on the 31st.

I drove by this cute farm, December 5th, and noticed their fabulous Christmas Trees.. I turned around at the next driveway. So glad I turned around. I found the most beautiful tree! When I went in to pay, they also included apple cider! I have to be honest and say I've lived in Maine for 52 years and have never had apple cider before. I was pleasantly surprised, it's so good! Thank you to the two ladies that were there.
So many apples for pick your own, with pumpkin patches as well. The store is so cute and I thought the prices were fair. We will definitely be back!!

Charm of an old country store.  Lots and lots of maine made preserves, syrups and honey and candies.
Wide assortment of Spices and dry beans.
Local dairy items and eggs
Plus Goods Potato Chips!!
Prices are fair and reasonable
Worth the trip...
This place this a sort of a country store. They have all kinds of goods inside as well as plants outside.
My absolute favorite place to go apple picking. The orchard is beautiful, the apples are delicious and the staff is always so kind. Take your family and check out the store after!
You can taste the love that goes into producing these farm fresh vegetables. Such a beautiful organic farm and amazing to see how it has grown over the years!
The owners could not be nicer and they grow the most lush and delicious produce. I‚Äôll be back again and again. Can‚Äôt wait to visit the farm stand again in summer 2025!
What a find! Have been a customer all summer long and loving it! Josh is great and the veggies are wonderful!

While, I have never been to the farm stand in Lyman, I have bought produce from Josh consistently at the Biddeford and Saco farmer's markets and have never been dissapointed! It is always the highest quality and he has a great nack for organizing his product beautifully. I plan to continue to seek him out for his produce!
Super friendly!  Great local produce!

reviews.text: Had the best time! Such a beautiful and tranquil blueberry orchard! So appreciate Wayne and his family‚Äôs hospitality. Loved the delicious berries! Enjoyed tasting such a wide variety‚Äî who knew! Great value for a beautiful delicious experience!
Impressive operation, super fun picking with my son today, look forward to next year's crop, thank you for your hard work!
Small wonderful pick-your-own blueberry farm. Like 7 different varieties. Nice
Beautiful tasty berries, many varieties, nice family farm!
In all ways, just lovely.

We went and bought our christmas tree there. Wanted to support a local business.  Absolutely terrible time dealing with the two men there. Asked simple questions and got short rude replies. The women however fantastic pleasant and helpful. Had them help us tie it on our car, told the older gentleman I couldn't have the window open because my two year old was sleeping (mind you it's 28 outside at 530 pm).  He then threw the rope at me and said he isn't doing it, I can tie it myself and walked away. Just shitty behavior from a miserable old man who obviously is gonna run it into the ground. Won't be going back.
Love this Farm Stand and Live Lobster stop. Great produce, local honey, mum's, perennials, apples, beans, etc, etc.

Last weekend my wife and I went there and tried to buy some lobsters. My wife asked the owner a simple question about the price of a Lobsters. The owner swore at her and kicked us out. He tried to fight with my wife outside the parking lot. I would never go there again. That behavior is completely unacceptable.

Tried to shop here today for pumpkins wanting to support a small business over Hannafords. Parking is awful and we were yelled at by an extremely rude worker who was driving a forklift. We didn't even stop to shop we just left because we were so horrified to be yelled at like that! Don't come here, go to O'Donnells down the street if you're looking for pumpkins they are much kinder there.
Great prices on their plants and on their seafood too!! Always get my fresh live lobster and clams there first time buying plans but definitely won't be my last!!

reviews.text: We look forward to coming every year!

Had alot of fun picking with the grands, i  thinks i ate as much as i picked, lol always fun memories, just need some coolwhip later and yummy!!!!

I don‚Äôt give my business to places that display their political fuse and Support a cult leader. I really hope you can get by with your 40 to 45% page. As your neighbor and fellow business owner what a horrible business.

reviews.text: I went for the first time last week and love it. Everything is so fresh, especially green beans. Really enjoyed my cooked green beans and went to get a whole bunch more today. I wish I knew this place sooner. It's a pretty reasonable price as well. Service is awesome. The lady will answer any questions you may have. I showed some of the pictures to my coworker, and they are already planning to swing by.
Beautiful assortment of Pumpkins, fruits and vegetables!!

Stopped by the farm stand on Route One on my way home from work and enjoyed the best-corn-ever at dinner that evening. Sweet and tender. Perfect! Definitely going to make this part of my routine. They have so much more produce for me to enjoy.
Very nice selection of pumpkins & gourds for the fall season
Had fun shopping there today! Big selection of vegetables, variety of hot or sweet peppers including poblanos. Wild blueberries! Great finds, thank you.

We started with lunch at our favorite food truck, Meet on the Street, and some delicious adult ciders. üçª Because it‚Äôs fall, y‚Äôall‚Äîwhy not! üçÇüçÅ Next, this well-run operation had golf carts to drive you to the field. üöú We enjoyed apple üçè and blueberry picking. I've missed Blueberry season last few years returning home to visit family, so when I saw Libby's was still open, we had to go. We got 10 lbs blueberries and 2 bags apples for a little over $100. But it was worth it because you can't find the flavor anywhere else across the states. My BFF and I had an amazing time and experience to last a lifetime. Beautiful farm and beautiful fruit. The only downfall I would say would be how everything is priced because it would be difficult for a big family to come and enjoy themselves because pricing is based on how many people are in your group. The fresh smoothies were delicious‚Ä¶as were the berries!   Well worth the drive from Portland.

placeDetails.name: Orchard Ridge Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 236 Sebago Lake Rd, Gorham, ME 04038, USA

reviews.text:
Popped into this super cute spot for the first time since the new owners took over, and I‚Äôm so glad I did! The menu is packed with options‚Äîwhether you're in the mood for a breakfast sandwich, a hot latte, fresh bagels, pizza, a burger, or even a salad. Plus, they‚Äôve got all sorts of fun pantry goodies, gifts, beer, wine, fresh eggs, and some chilled and frozen items.

While you wait for your food, you can wander outside to say hey to the chickens, goats, donkey, and pig!

We decided to hang out and had lunch at the big table that fits 4-6 people. We tried a little bit of everything: breakfast sandwich, pizza, burger, and falafel wrap. Everything was soooo tasty! There are also a couple of bar seats if you want to grab a quick bite. Can‚Äôt wait to come back!

Went on a first date here. And it was amazing. Sadly, the apple picking was dwindling down. And the apples got some weather damage.  But we found a couple. The property is beautiful üòç.  Just a walk through the orchard was so peaceful. The shop had some yummy coffee drinks too! Service there is so friendly.

Really enjoyed staying here overnight in my camper and sampling some yummy meals and also enjoyed watching families enjoy immersing themselves in the experience of apple picking and friendly encounters with farm animals. Also, they are decorated for Halloween and have beautiful pumpkins and marigolds for sale. The apple trees were prolific but unfortunately the recent hurricane toppled some trees and lost many apples to the ground early.  The farm is lovely and right on the Sebago to sea greenway which I took advantage of with my dog. My dog is good with farm animals but still, I kept her up because of the food service & young families ( There is a playground and lawn games in the picnic area too). The staff work hard and are friendly and helpful. Market has an abundant variety of homegrown fresh foods and treats!

Well....the orchard had only 2 varieties of apples. For $3 per pound, I expected a lot more. And, I was sad to see the animals' living conditions. The chickens were too crowded in their pen, the 2 goats didn't have any grazing area to speak of, and the one pig had no water in its small pen. There was a friendly rabbit hopping around.

The store was very nice, with lots of gourmet goodies and an impressive array of meats. The one staff person we saw was very friendly.  A nice display of pumpkins was outside.  But their website offered a much better experience!

This is a great little farm stand/market with all the best local items has a surprisingly good kitchen that somehow serves up the best bagels and cream cheese I've ever had. Great for apple picking, pumpkins etc. in season, but a necessary stop at least for the bagels (and whatever else the market might offer) when I'm in the neighborhood.
Great experience and loved the variety of apples available
Staff is always helpful and friendly, and they have great local produce at reasonable prices. I love Randall's!

They have very very best apple cider donuts üç© & apple cider in Standish Maine , you can pick your own apples or buy them inside . you can buy maple syrup, honey , fruit, vegetables, jams, üåΩ, blueberry, strawberries, Christmas trees in winter time
If you are visiting Maine come here
Nice place to get apples and cider that doesn't have a preserved in it
Always so nice and their cider and donuts are great!

Name: Saco River Farms

placeDetails.name: Saco River Farms
placeDetails.formatted_address: 29 Weeman Rd, Steep Falls, ME 04085, USA

reviews.text: I wish I could give this place higher than a five star! Only place that I can find goat meat that is worth buying. Had a fantastic conversation with who I assume is the owner and he was just fantastic! I was going to try some pickled carrots from a brand I do not know and he convinced me with his rave reviews to try the other flavor. Let me tell you they were fantastic! He was super knowledgeable and super friendly. I just wish it was closer lol I can‚Äôt wait to go get more of the carrots.

The farmstead has a great selection of meat and goat dairy products. The farm is not open to the public, they really don't like it if you go to the animal area.  If you are looking to see goats don't come here, go to Sunflower Farm Creamery instead. However if you are looking for meat and dairy products this is better.
Nice farm stand!  Goat meat and goat gelato, goat yogurt! Just what I was looking for. They also have duck, beef, and variety of pickled products.

Came here on Saturday looking for a local meat market- I don‚Äôt know how I haven‚Äôt heard of this place before. I wish I could add a video of how juicy these goat carnitas I made are. It‚Äôs no more expensive than Whole Foods, they‚Äôre a small local business and the products are so so good. I got a small roast (3-4 lbs) and slow cooked it for 10 hours, it melts in your mouth. Made rice bowls and burritos. Also picked up some of their homemade cajeta which is usually impossible to find in rural areas. It‚Äôs so mf good, I could probably drink it. The raw goat milk they do is delicious and not overly ‚Äúgoat-y‚Äù (as people say), it‚Äôs creamy and light. Check the spot out, there‚Äôs a wide variety of products and the dude who runs the place (I think?) is super friendly and helpful.  I‚Äôll be back for sausages and maybe some pork cuts and duck eggs soon, great spot. Would love to meet the goats!

Five stars! As much as I‚Äôd love to hide this farm for myself, I‚Äôm left salivating for more after consuming everything I bought three days ago.

It‚Äôs important to note that I am normally not a goat cheese fan. I am converted forever.

The store is small and packed with delicious charcuterie foods like meats, spreads, crackers and cheeses from Maine. The wine and beer selections are wonderful and handpicked by the owners. They make their own goat cheeses that are AHüëèüèºMAYüëèüèºZINGüëèüèº. The cheddars, valencay, and mizithra are the reason I will return regularly. Smooth, full-bodied flavors make these cheeses easy to pair and easy to just spoon feed yourself.

They also offer produce and frozen meats from great Maine farms. I highly recommend you give these wonderful people your business for gifts for loved ones and to up your cooking game. 11/10

reviews.text: Great selection, fresh, local,  friendly,  glad I stopped in! üôÇ
We've been getting our fresh produce from this farm for as long as I can remember. Prices are reasonable and staff is friendly and helpful. Can't go wrong here. Open daily during season 10-6.
Just a small local farm stand, been there for years, just like to help out local people
Wonderful vegetables, wonderful people, salt of the earth. We've been coming here for at least 20 years.

Pizza is fresh and elderberry syrups saved me. If you work with covid regardless of the specialty. They have elderberry in juices and syrups. My family thanks you for helping me keep my immunity up with all your fresh veggies and elderberry products.

Love this store. The meats and produce... AWESOME!
Save gas. Visit this friendly local farm stand with veggies, flowers and honey.  We got all we needed.

The best farm to jar jam on the planet!!! They know me as the "crazy guy from NJ"  who will drive up to buy their stuff at the weekly Farmers Market. Just don't buy their triple berry - save them all for me lol.
Super friendly and always a pleasure to deal with and they always go out of their way to accommodate.

We DID just learn they come up for the Portland Farmer's Market in Deering Oaks, so once we get a better idea of what space we have, we're gonna have to stop in and see them there!
I go here every year and they are fantastic.  Super friendly owners and plants that always produce.
Visit this local farm stand for your vegetables, flowers and honey.  Super nice with lots of options.
